abstract_ssm: The Co-Operative Educational Instite Association in the Brownsville neighborhood of Brooklyn, New York City, administered a cooperative evening school offering high school equivalency courses. The records consist of reports, minutes, schedules, and correspondence that document the life of the school.
corpname_ssm: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives
